Greek Stocks: Motor Oil Hellas, Coca-Cola HBC Shares Are Active

-- B y   P a u l   T u g w e l l
-- 
2011-03-17T09:40:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/greek-stocks-motor-oil-hellas-coca-cola-hbc-shares-are-active.html
  Greece ’s benchmark ASE Index
advanced 11.20, or 0.7 percent, to 1,622.29 at 11:23 a.m. in
Athens, its second day of gains.  The FTSE/ASE 20 Index of the country’s biggest companies
also added 0.7 percent to 757.58. The Cyprus General Market
Index gained dropped 0.3 percent to 1056.35.  The following shares were the most active in Athens trading
today. Symbols are in parentheses.  Coca-Cola Hellenic Bottling Co. SA (EEEK GA) rose 0.8
percent to 19.53 euros. The world’s second-largest bottler of
Coke products said in an e-mailed statement that chief operating
officer Dimitris Lois will become chief executive officer in the
third quarter of this year when CEO Doros Constantinou retires.  Motor Oil Hellas SA (MOH GA) gained 2.7 percent to 8.76
euros. Greece’s second-largest refiner posted a profit of 131
million euros in 2010 compared with 107.8 million euros a year
earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Tugwell in  Athens  at 
